Steps to get started with Django on Heroku
1. Create an account at heroku.com
2. Create and start a python virtualenv http://pypi.python.org/pypi/virtualenv
    a) easy_install virtualenv #first time only
    b) mkdir ~/Documents/PythonEnv/ && cd ~/Documents/PythonEnv/
    c) virtualenv --no-site-packages project-name
    d) source ~/Documents/PythonEnv/project-name/bin/activate
3. git clone git@github.com:rfadams/python-django-heroku.git ~/projects/project-name
4. cd ~/projects/project-name && pip install -r requirements.txt
5. python web/manage.py runserver
6. Install the heroku CLI http://devcenter.heroku.com/articles/heroku-command
7. heroku create --stack cedar project-name
8. heroku config:add DJANGO_ENV=production
9. git push heroku master
8. heroku open
 
#Optional
9. mysqladmin -u DBUSER -p create projectdb

#Assumes you're gonna use South for database management / migrations. http://south.aeracode.org/docs/tutorial/part1.html
10. Uncomment 'south' from the bottom of INSTALLED_APPS in web/settings.py
10. python web/manage.py syncdb
11. python web/manage.py startapp southtut #Then make a new model
12. python web/manage.py schemamigration southtut --initial
13. python web/manage.py migrate southtut
14. python web/manage.py schemamigration southtut --auto #After you make some changes
15. python web/manage.py migrate southtut